1 crime involving moral turpitude;
2 (b) Is able to speak and understand the English language or a
3 language understood by a substantial portion of the facility residents;
4 and
5 (c) Has successfully completed a basic course of training approved
6 by the department for nurse aides within one hundred twenty days of
7 initial employment in the capacity of a nurse aide.
8 (2)(a) A registered nurse or licensed practical nurse whose license
9 has been revoked, suspended, or voluntarily surrendered in lieu of
10 discipline may not act as a nurse aide for a service provider or in a
11 facility described in subsection (1) of this section.
12 (b) If a person registered as a nurse aide becomes licensed as a
13 registered nurse or licensed practical nurse, his or her registration as
14 a nurse aide becomes null and void as of the date of licensure.
15 (c) A person listed on the Nurse Aide Registry with respect to whom
16 a finding of conviction has been placed on the registry may petition the
17 department to have such finding removed at any time after one year has
18 elapsed since the date such finding was placed on the registry.
19 (3) The department may prescribe a curriculum for training nurse
20 aides and may adopt and promulgate rules and regulations for such courses
21 of training. The content of the courses of training and competency
22 evaluation programs shall be consistent with federal requirements unless
23 exempted. The department may approve courses of training if such courses
24 of training meet the requirements of this section. Such courses of
25 training shall include instruction on the responsibility of each nurse
26 aide to report suspected abuse or neglect pursuant to sections 28-372 and
27 28-711. Nursing homes may carry out approved courses of training within
28 the nursing home, except that nursing homes may not conduct the
29 competency evaluation part of the program. The prescribed training shall
30 be administered by a licensed registered nurse.
31 (4) For nurse aides at intermediate care facilities for persons with
-3-

