1 developmental disabilities, such courses of training shall be no less
2 than twenty hours in duration and shall include at least fifteen hours of
3 basic personal care training and five hours of basic therapeutic and
4 emergency procedure training, and for nurse aides at all nursing homes
5 other than intermediate care facilities for persons with developmental
6 disabilities, such courses shall be no less than seventy-five hours in
7 duration.
8 (5) This section shall not prohibit any facility from exceeding the
9 minimum hourly or training requirements.
10 Sec. 3. Original sections 71-6038 and 71-6039, Reissue Revised
11 Statutes of Nebraska, are repealed.
